<protolog id="rid.12479_nm.21313" type="description" xmlns="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://namesforlife.com/ns/protolog file:/C:/NamesforLife/workspace/namesforlife-schema/protolog.xsd"><organism doi="10.1601/nm.21313" exemplar-doi="10.1601/ex.21313" rank="species">Methylovulum miyakonense</organism><reference id="rid.12479"><citation citation-type="journal"><authors><person-name><surname>Iguchi</surname><given-names>H.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Yurimoto</surname><given-names>H.</given-names></person-name><person-name><surname>Sakai</surname><given-names>Y.</given-names></person-name></authors><article-title>Methylovulum miyakonense gen. nov., sp. nov., a type I methanotroph isolated from forest soil</article-title><year>2011</year><volume>61</volume><issue>4</issue><fpage>810</fpage><lpage>815</lpage><source id="117">International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology</source><abbrev>Int J Syst Evol Microbiol</abbrev><issn>1466-5026</issn><essn>1466-5034</essn><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1099/ijs.0.019604-0</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">20435749</pub-id></citation></reference><content><p class="title"><s>Description of <em>Methylovulum miyakonense</em> sp. nov.</s></p><p class="etymology"><s><em>Methylovulum miyakonense</em> (mi.ya.ko.nen′se. N.L. neut. adj. <em>miyakonense</em> of, or belonging to, Miyako, the ancient capital Kyoto).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Characteristics are as described for the genus with the following additions.</s><s>Cells are 1.5–2.5×1.0–2.0 µm.</s><s>Grows optimally at 24–32 °C and pH 6.5.</s><s>Sensitive to NaCl above 0.2 % (w/v).</s></p><p class="description"><s>The type strain, HT12<sup>T</sup> ( = NBRC 106162<sup>T</sup>  = DSM 23269<sup>T</sup>  = ATCC BAA-2070<sup>T</sup>), was isolated from forest soil in Japan.</s></p></content></protolog>